  "coverage": "Found 1X2 three-way decimal odds for 28 group-stage fixtures across the 13-20 June 2026 window — essentially every match in that window. All odds were sourced as American moneyline or UK fractional odds and converted to decimal by me (positive American X -> X/100+1; negative American X -> 100/|X|+1; fractional a/b -> a/b+1). Bookmaker attribution: Oddschecker (aggregator best-price), ESPN, DraftKings, and Bet365 as noted per row; where a search aggregated multiple books I attributed to the named source. Caveats: (1) Oddschecker and Oddspedia direct pages returned HTTP 403, so most odds come via WebSearch summaries of those pages and via ESPN match odds pages rather than direct scrapes — values are snapshots and live odds drift. (2) Home/away orientation follows the official ESPN/Sky fixture listing (first-listed team = home); some sportsbook pages list teams in the opposite order (e.g. ESPN gameId 760432 lists Senegal first), but odds were mapped to the correct team. (3) Match dates have minor cross-source timezone discrepancies (matches kicking off late ET appear on the next calendar day in some UK listings); I used the predominant North American local match date. Fields I could not verify per-book to the exact line are still real published odds rounded to standard decimal. Nothing was set to null because a credible three-way price was found for every listed fixture."
 },
